Package: python-actp
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${python:Depends}
Description: Adaptive Clearing Tool Path Library
 FreeSteel is a program originally written by Julian Todd and Martin
 Dunschen and released under the GPL.  It generated an adaptive clearing
 strategy tool path for screen display.
 .
 The libactp (Adaptive Clearing Tool Path Library) is an implementation
 of the GPL'ed algorithm demonstrated in FreeSteel as a set of C library
 functions. This library can then be wrapped for use in other languages
 such as Python or Perl.
 .
 This package contains the Python module.
 .

